OL,5, Batteries thrown in household rubbish  
OL,6, bins cause about 700 fires every year  
OL,7, in dustcarts and waste-processing      
OL,8, centres, local authorities say.        
OL,10,FLithium-ion batteries can explode if   
OL,11,Fdamaged or crushed.                    
OL,13,FThe Environmental Services Association 
OL,14,Fsays resulting fires cost fire services
OL,15,Fand waste operators some #158m a year. 
OL,17,FNon-profit organisation Material Focus,
OL,18,Fwhich surveyed local authorities, runs 
OL,19,Fan online search tool to help people   
OL,20,Ffind their nearest recycling point.    
